  "riddle": "Here is the riddle:\n\n1. Begin your journey with the chronicler of post-war American literature, a critic ever watchful in his philosophical gaze, known as an authoritative analyst of the works that shaped the 20th century’s cultural landscape — a scholar who dissected the beats and arcs of time. From his article, how many tongues has its wisdom been rendered into?\n\n2. Take that numeral tally. Imagine it carved in stone during Caesar's era. How many strokes of the chisel made it?\n\n3. A beacon of learning stands firm since its birth in the 19th century, nestled 'neath the Ann Arbor skies. In what year did its journey commence?\n\n4. Reverse the digits of that founding year — what new number emerges when history flips its script?\n\n5. High above the equatorial lands of samba and rhythm, a city designed by Lucio Costa seeks the skies. Measure the altitude where its heart beats the proudest — what is its elevation?\n\n6. That viral siege which gripped the globe has many stories to tell. What count of sections array beneath the surface of its annals?\n\n7. As economies trembled and reset, a certain downturn's causes are analyzed in prose. What's the numeric slot that holds these ponderings in its table of knowledge?\n\n8. Across the azure Atlantic, a Spanish set of seven awaits. What height do the peaks of these islands claim from sea level?\n\n9. As the numerals from clue 1, clue 2, clue 4, and clue 7 interlace like lines in a stanza, calculate this: take the distance between them born of Caesar's legacy, and the cause in our economic saga, wrapped in digits reversed — what single numeral crowns this voyage, calculated thus: abs(3 - 3) % 10?",
